linux will save the following type log information: kernal, service, applications;

rsyslog: service rsyslog status;

rsyslog configuration file: /etc/rsyslog.conf;

logfile location: /var/log

view logfile: tail -f 

facility: define the source of log information, in order to classify log info. type: kernal, user, mail, daemon, auth, syslog...

priority/severity level: emergency, alert, critical, error, warning, notice, informational, debug.

configuring rsyslog: "facility.priority        log_location"

send and save logfile into a internet server: *.*  @@192.168.1.1 (TCP protocol)
